Package: seqTrimR
Type: Package
Title: Sequence trimming tool
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Christopher Nobles, Ph.D.
Maintainer: Christopher Nobles <cnobles@pennmedicine.upenn.edu>
Description: Tool trimming fasta or fastq sequences. 5' trimming, or leading 
    trimming, as well as 3', or overreading, trimming can be controlled through
    ambiguous nucleotide code (IUPAC) as well as declaring mismatches. This tool
    can extract sequences from reads as well, denoted by serial 'N' sequences 
    within input leading trimming sequences.
License: GNU General Public License v3
LazyData: TRUE
Depends:
    ShortRead,
    stringr,
    argparse,
    pander,
    yaml,
    parallel
